text: That's really not enough to make you a fan?

Very true. 
It's his "If you think I'm good at building rockets, wait until you see my stand-up comedy" that drives him into the ditch.
Musk saying "I can do better at democratic politics than Trump" is an exact analog of Trump saying "I'm better at building electric cars than Musk."

The only purist 'tech-right' political philosophy is (some variant of) NRx.  Trouble is, MAGA is way too good at democratic politics for imminent collapse and 'start-up regime' alternatives to have any realistic space. (There's more chance for seasteads, charter cities, and Antarctic burrows than anything in the continental USA, which isn't to say there's a lot.)  Dealing with this reality is the current test. Much stumbling over it in process.

... Flexible deference to the populist right is the only practical option currently. Sure, keep working on the exotic Capital Escapology efforts, but they belong in the secret subterranean lab for now. They'll get their chance eventually, under right populist conditions more probably than under woke leftist ones.
Lemurs far more sympathetic to "Weave Left and Right" than I am, but the symmetrical hands point is good.
Yes. They deserve far more attention. This truly immense (and exploding) labor shortage puts the AI jobs panic in a very different context.
Skull-splitting hangover from this silliness is going to be staggering.
